<L>__{exterior embassy (day) medium shot}
<A>__{he leans out the door and beckons the draytons and hank to come in quickly. the three get out of the car and hurry toward the door.}
<L>__{interior embassy kitchen (day) med. shot}
<A>__{the man moves back into the kitchen, and goes to stand guard at the doorway through which the workers left. the door is closed.}
<L>__{interior embassy corridor (day) med. close shot}
<A>__{the servants are packed together at one side of the corridor. they are talking, grumbling.}
<C>__{woman cook}
<D>__{this embassy there's always something queer going on.}
<L>__{interior embassy corridor (day) close shot}
<A>__{while the other servants are grumbling, one is saying nothing. he rather a shrewd looking young footman. he strains to listen through closed door. coming from the kitchen are several sounds. a door opening, the walking of feet, and finally the slam of a door.}
<C>__{another voice}
<D>__{bringing people in, in secret...}
<C>__{another voice}
<D>__{give me the swiss embassy every time, there's neutrality for you!}
<A>__{then the sound of a car leaving outside. the door to the kitchen opens and the servants, including the young footman enter again.}
